data.name: TrDissolve_0
data.value: Transforms line feature class 'featureClass' by dissolving connected features

data.name: TrDissolve_Attributes
data.value: Attributes to be transferred to transformed feature class. Must be used with alias and group expression, i.e. 'MAX(LAUF_NR) AS MAX_LAUF_NR'. In the resulting feature class, only attributes defined in 'Attributes' or 'GroupBy' can be used.

data.name: TrDissolve_Constraint
data.value: Only feature that fulfill constraint between each other are dissolved

data.name: TrDissolve_CreateMultipartFeatures
data.value: (Default = false) - false: create separate features when 3 or more features are connected. Only connections with 2 features are dissolved. - true: create multipart features for all connected source features.

data.name: TrDissolve_featureClass
data.value: Line feature class to dissolve

data.name: TrDissolve_GroupBy
data.value: Group features by 'GroupBy' before dissolving In the resulting feature class, only attributes defined in 'Attributes' or 'GroupBy' can be used.

data.name: TrDissolve_NeighborSearchOption
data.value: (Default = Tile) -Tile: dissolve features only within the current tile - All: if features start/end outside tile, load additional connected features (recursively)

data.name: TrDissolve_SearchDistance
data.value: Additional distance to cache 'featureClass' features per tile

data.name: TrFootprint_0
data.value: Transforms multipatches to polygons by taking their footprints

data.name: TrFootprint_multipatchClass
data.value: multipatch feature class to transform

data.name: TrGeometryToPoints_0
data.value: Transforms geometries to points. The transformed feature class has the attribute PartIndex and VertexIndex. These fields index from which polygon part the transformed polygon part was generated

data.name: TrGeometryToPoints_component
data.value: GeometryComponent to extract

data.name: TrGeometryToPoints_featureClass
data.value: multipoint, line, polygon or multipatch class to transform

data.name: TrGeometryTransform_Attributes
data.value: Attributes that are copied from source featureclass to resulting featureclass

data.name: TrIntersect_0
data.value: Transforms features of 'intersected' by intersecting them with features from 'intersecting'. If intersected is a line class and intersecting is a polygon class, then the resulting feature class has an attribute 'PartIntersected' which contains the (resultingFeature.Shape.Length / intersectedFeature.Shape.Length)

data.name: TrIntersect_intersected
data.value: Feature class. The attributes of 'intersected' can be accessed by 't0.<field>' in the resulting featureClass

data.name: TrIntersect_intersecting
data.value: Feature class. The attributes of 'intersecting' can be accessed by 't1.<field>' in the resulting featureClass

data.name: TrLineToPolygon_0
data.value: Transforms closed lines of 'closedLineClass' to polygons

data.name: TrLineToPolygon_closedLineClass
data.value: line feature class to transform

data.name: TrLineToPolygon_PolylineUsage
data.value: Defines how to handle not closed lines - AsPolygonIfClosedElseIgnore (default) : ignore not closed lines

data.name: TrMakeTable_0
data.value: Creates a table from an existing table or view in the database. This allows using tables that would otherwise not be usable because they have not been harvested as datasets in the data dictionary. Typical examples are: - Association tables in many-to-many relationship classes - Tables or views that are not part of the geodatabase. If the table is part of the geodatabase and registered as versioned it will be opened from the same version as the base table.

data.name: TrMakeTable_1
data.value: Creates a table from an SQL statement directly evaluated in the RDBMS. The same restrictions apply as for ArcGIS 'query layers'. For example, versioned data cannot be accessed, only the raw tables in the database including tables that are not registered as part of the geodatabase.

data.name: TrMakeTable_baseTable
data.value: A table from the same data model. This table will be used to determine the workspace of the table.

data.name: TrMakeTable_objectIdField
data.value: The field name containing the non-null and unique values to be used as identifier.

data.name: TrMakeTable_sql
data.value: The SQL statement to be evaluated in the database. Example: SELECT ID, REGION, LAUF_NR, STATUS FROM TLM.GEWISS_LAUF_REGION WHERE REGION <> 'LI' AND LAUF_NR IN (SELECT LAUF_NR FROM TLM.GEWISS_LAUF_EXTERNAL WHERE OWNER = 'KANTON')

data.name: TrMakeTable_viewOrTableName
data.value: The name of the database object to be created and made usable as table.

data.name: TrCombinedFilter_0
data.value: Creates a filtered feature class based on several other filters that use the same 'featureClassToFilter'.

data.name: TrCombinedFilter_expression
data.value: An expression that allows combining input filters with AND or OR. An input filter which is passed by a feature evaluates to 'true', a filter that excludes a feature evaluates to 'false'. The input filters are referenced by the transformer configuration name. If not specified, all input filters are combined with AND, i.e. the feature must pass all filters to be in the result. Example to get all islands in Bavaria: (islands_in_lakes OR islands_in_rivers) AND islands_in_bavaria islands_in_lakes uses the OnlyContained transformer with 'containing' feature class Lakes (polygon) islands_in_rivers uses the OnlyContained transformer with 'containing' feature class Rivers (polygon) islands_in_bavaria uses the OnlyIntersecting transformer with 'intersecting' feature class States (polygon) with constraint NAME = 'Bayern'

data.name: TrCombinedFilter_featureClassToFilter
data.value: The feature class to be filtered.

data.name: TrCombinedFilter_inputFilters
data.value: The filters which should be checked to determine if a feature passes the filter. By default, a feature passes the filter if it passes all input filters.

data.name: TrMultilineToLine_0
data.value: Transforms multipart lines to single lines. The transformed feature class has the attribute PartIndex. This field index from which line part the transformed line was generated

data.name: TrMultilineToLine_featureClass
data.value: line feature class to transform

data.name: TrMultipolygonToPolygon_0
data.value: Transforms multipart polygons to single polygons. The transformed feature class has the attributes OuterRingIndex and InnerRingIndex. These fields index from which polygon part the transformed polygon was generated. The transformed feature class has also the attributes of 'featureClass', which can be accessed by 't0.<fieldName>'.

data.name: TrMultipolygonToPolygon_featureClass
data.value: polygon feature class to transform

data.name: TrMultipolygonToPolygon_TransformedParts
data.value: Default = SinglePolygons -SinglePolygon: converts multi polygon to single polygons (Remark: InnerRingIndex = -2) -OuterRings: converts all out rings to polygons (Remark: InnerRingIndex = -1) -InnerRings: converts all inner rings to polygons -AllRings: converts all rings to polygons (Remark: polygons generated from outer rings: InnerRingIndex = -1)

data.name: TrOnlyContainedFeatures_0
data.value: Creates a filtered feature class containing only the features that are contained within features from 'containing'. The resulting feature class has the same properties and attributes as 'featureClassToFilter'.

data.name: TrOnlyContainedFeatures_containing
data.value: The features used to check if they contain the features to be filtered.

data.name: TrOnlyContainedFeatures_featureClassToFilter
data.value: The feature class to be filtered.

data.name: TrOnlyIntersectingFeatures_0
data.value: Creates a filtered feature class containing only the features that intersect features from 'intersecting'. The resulting feature class has the same properties and attributes as 'featureClassToFilter'.

data.name: TrOnlyIntersectingFeatures_featureClassToFilter
data.value: The feature class to be filtered.

data.name: TrOnlyIntersectingFeatures_intersecting
data.value: The features used to check if they intersect the features to be filtered.

data.name: TrPolygonToLine_0
data.value: Transform polygon to line by taking the boundary of the polygons in 'featureClass'. The transformed feature class has also the attributes of 'featureClass', which can be accessed by 't0.<fieldName>'.

data.name: TrPolygonToLine_featureClass
data.value: polygon feature class

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_0
data.value: Transforms features of 't0' and features of 't1' to features, with shape of 't0' if they intersect.

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_Constraint
data.value: Constraint on spatially joined features. Only spatially joined feature pairs that fulfill the constraint will be transformed to resulting features. The involved features are aliased using "T0" and T1". Example: T0.Level = T1.Level

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_Grouped
data.value: Default = false. If false: create one feature for each (t0,t1)-feature pair that intersects if true: create one feature for each feature in 't0', that intersects any feature of 't1'

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_NeighborSearchOption
data.value: (Default = Tile) -Tile: join features only within the current tile - All: if features lie partially outside tile, load additional connected features

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_OuterJoin
data.value: Default = false.Left outer Join. If true: transform features from t0-features that have no spatial relation to any feature of t1 If false: ignore features from t0 that have no spatial relation to any feature of t1

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_t0
data.value: Feature class that provides the shape for the new features

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_T0Attributes
data.value: Attributes of 't0' that are transferred to transformed feature class. Can be used with alias, i.e. 'TLM.TLM_GEWAESSER_LAUF.LAUF_NR AS T1_LAUF_NR'. In the resulting feature class, only attributes defined in T0Attributes or T1Attributes can be used.

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_t1
data.value: Feature class to join

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_T1Attributes
data.value: See T0Attributes. If 'Grouped'=true, the attributes must be defined by Group-Expressions like COUNT(),MIN(),MAX()... Remark: Group expressions can only contain a single field expression. If a more complex expression is needed, use the parameter T1CalcAttributes. Example: Count the number of joined features with a specific objecttype 'x' would be: T1CalcAttributes: "IIF(objecttype='x',1,0) AS X_VALUE" T1Attributes: "SUM(X_VALUE) AS X_COUNT"

data.name: TrSpatialJoin_T1CalcAttributes
data.value: Calculations with attributes of 't1' that are used in Group-Expressions. See T1Attributes

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_0
data.value: Creates a joined table with the fields from 'leftTable' and 'rightTable'.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_joinType
data.value: The type of join. Currently inner joins and left joins are supported.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_leftTable
data.value: The left table in the join. Its OBJECTID field will be used in the result table. If it is a FeatureClass its shape field it will be used in the result FeatureClass.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_leftTableKey
data.value: The key field in the left table.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_manyToManyTable
data.value: The association / bridge table for a many-to-many join.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_manyToManyTableLeftKey
data.value: The key field in the many-to-many association table referencing the leftTableKey.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_manyToManyTableRightKey
data.value: The key field in the many-to-many association table referencing the rightTableKey.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_rightTable
data.value: The right table in the join.

data.name: TrTableJoinInMemory_rightTableKey
data.value: The key field in the right table.

data.name: TrTableJoin_0
data.value: Transforms table 't0' and table 't1', which must be related by 'relationName', to a joined table

data.name: TrTableJoin_joinType
data.value: JoinType

data.name: TrTableJoin_relationName
data.value: name of existing relation between 't0' and 't1'

data.name: TrTableJoin_t0
data.value: table to join with 't1'

data.name: TrTableJoin_t1
data.value: table to join with 'leftTable'

data.name: TrOnlyDisjointFeatures_0
data.value: Creates a filtered feature class containing only the features that are disjoint from features from 'disjoint'. Features that intersect any feature from 'disjoint' are filtered out. The resulting feature class has the same properties and attributes as 'featureClassToFilter'.

data.name: TrOnlyDisjointFeatures_disjoint
data.value: The features used to check if they are disjoint from the features to be filtered.

data.name: TrOnlyDisjointFeatures_featureClassToFilter
data.value: The feature class to be filtered.

data.name: TrSpatiallyFiltered_FilteringSearchOption
data.value: (Default = Tile) -Tile: search for spatially related features only using the current tile - All: search for spatially related features in the entire filtering featureClass

data.name: TrFootprint_Tolerance
data.value: The tolerance for the footprint calculation. The vertices of a multipatch geometry should not be closer than the tolerance to any other vertex or segment of the same geometry. If a value below 0 is specified, the tolerance of the multipatchClass is used.

data.name: TrGetNodes_0
data.value: Get unique endpoints of 'lineClass'

data.name: TrGetNodes_Attributes
data.value: Attributes to be transferred to transformed feature class. Must be used with alias and group expression, i.e. 'MAX(LAUF_NR) AS MAX_LAUF_NR'. In the resulting feature class, only attributes defined in 'Attributes' can be used.

data.name: TrGetNodes_lineClass
data.value: Line FeatureClass

data.name: TrZAssign_0
data.value: Creates a featureclass, where the height of vertices correspond to 'raster'. Remark: the height is only assign within each processsed tile.

data.name: TrZAssign_featureClass
data.value: featureclass to assign the raster z-values

data.name: TrZAssign_raster
data.value: raster with z-Values

data.name: TrZAssign_rasterMosaic
data.value: raster mosaic with z-Values

data.name: TrZAssign_ZAssignOption
data.value: whether the z-values shall be assigned to vertices within the current tile only or to all vertices (slower).

data.name: TrProject_0
data.value: Transforms the geometries of the featureClass to a new spatial reference defined by the targetSpatialReferenceId. The transformed feature class retains the attributes of the original featureClass, which can be accessed using t0.<fieldName>.

data.name: TrProject_featureClass
data.value: The feature class containing the geometries to be transformed. The geometries in this feature class will be projected to the spatial reference defined by the targetSpatialReferenceId.

data.name: TrProject_targetSpatialReferenceId
data.value: The ID of the target spatial reference to which the geometries in the featureClass will be projected. This ID corresponds to a specific coordinate system or projection, such as WGS 84 or another predefined spatial reference system.
